Lone Star  Funds, the Dallas-based
firm that invests in non-performing mortgages and other real
estate-related assets, is set to finish raising a $5 billion
fund today, a person with knowledge of the situation said.  Demand from investors to put money in Fund VIII exceeded
the $5 billion maximum set by Lone Star, led by founder  John Grayken , said the person, who asked not to be named because the
information is private.  Jed Repko, a spokesman for Lone Star at public relations
firm Joele Frank, Wilkinson Brimmer Katcher, declined to comment
